<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 3:43AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Clay and
east central Archer Counties through 415 AM CDT...
At 343 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Scotland, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Henrietta, Scotland, Windthorst, Lake Arrowhead and Bluegrove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
